</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[789,879,1805,1830]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[789,879,1805,1830]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
from all other 
<taxonomicName box="[1046,1151,1805,1829]" class="Insecta" family="Nepticulidae" genus="Stigmella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1046,1151,1805,1829]" italics="true" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Stigmella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="57" lastPageNumber="58" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="53.[151,1436,1697,2010]" lastBlockId="54.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="54" lastPageNumber="55" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,260,1841,1866]" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[277,377,1841,1866]" captionStart="FIGURES 152 – 156" captionStartId="56.[151,264,1800,1823]" captionTargetBox="[159,1426,193,1770]" captionTargetId="figure@56.[159,1426,193,1773]" captionTargetPageId="56" captionText="FIGURES 152 – 156. Stigmella ampla Diškus &amp; Stonis, sp. nov. 152, holotype, male adult; 153, same, genitalia, slide no. AD 645, transtilla; 154, same, valvae; 155, same, capsule with phallus removed; 156, same, phallus (ZMUC)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/164278/files/figure.png" pageId="53" pageNumber="54">Fig. 152</figureCitation>
). Forewing length about 
<quantity box="[664,755,1841,1866]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.1" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="5.1">5.1 mm</quantity>
; wingspan about 
<quantity box="[956,1123,1842,1866]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.085" metricValueMax="1.09" metricValueMin="1.08" pageId="53" pageNumber="54" unit="mm" value="10.85" valueMax="10.9" valueMin="10.8">10.8–10.9 mm</quantity>
. Head: palpi cream; frontal tuft comprised of dark grey-brown and cream scales (the latter prevail); collar cream; scape cream with some brown scales; antenna distinctly longer than half the length of forewing; flagellum with 48 segments, grey-brown, golden glossy on upper side and underside. Thorax and tegula golden cream, with some brown scales. Forewing golden cream, irregularly speckled with grey-brown scales with weak purple iridescence; fringe golden cream; underside of forewing grey-brown, with no spots. Hindwing and its fringe pale brown on upper side and underside, with no spots or androconia. Legs glossy cream, darkened with grey-brown on upper side. Abdomen brown on upper side, brownish cream on underside; tufts cream; genital segments brownish cream.
</paragraph>
